ðŸ§© Step 1: Update system packages
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

ðŸ§© Step 2: Install required dependencies
sudo apt install wget gpg apt-transport-https software-properties-common -y

ðŸ§© Step 3: Import the Microsoft GPG key
wget -qO- https://packages.microsoft.com/keys/microsoft.asc | gpg --dearmor > packages.microsoft.gpg
sudo install -o root -g root -m 644 packages.microsoft.gpg /usr/share/keyrings/

ðŸ§© Step 4: Add the VS Code repository
sudo sh -c 'echo "deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/packages.microsoft.gpg] https://packages.microsoft.com/repos/code stable main" > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/vscode.list'

ðŸ§© Step 5: Update package list again
sudo apt update

ðŸ§© Step 6: Install Visual Studio Code
sudo apt install code -y

ðŸ§© Step 7: Launch VS Code

You can now open it by typing:

code


or, if you want to open your current project folder:

code .


